   417	---
   418	
   419	## US Splitting Rationale
   420	- **Pillar Splitting:** Stories are split by the four pillars (Reference, Tracker, Reconstitution, Ordering) to allow incremental delivery of value.
   421	- **Admin vs User:** Managed user functionality is split from super admin functionality.
   422	- **Security/Offline:** Critical non-functional requirements like Auth and PWA are elevated to Epic 6 to ensure they are prioritized as foundational.
   423	
   424	## Dependency Graph (High Level)
   425	- `US-AUT-03` (Registration) -> Foundation for all other stories.
   426	- `US-TRK-01` (Create Protocol) -> depends on `US-REF-01` (View Compound)
   427	- `US-REC-02` (Record Reconstitution) -> depends on `US-REC-01` (Calculate)
   428	- `US-ORD-03` (Send Order) -> depends on `US-ORD-01` (Telegram MTProto)
   429	- `US-ADM-01` (Managed User) -> depends on `US-AUT-03` (Auth)

