    10	
    11	## 1. Global Standards
    12	
    13	### 1.1 Style & Idempotency
    14	- **Style**: RESTful Route Handlers (`app/api/*`) and Type-safe Server Actions (`app/actions/*`).
    15	- **Idempotency**: All mutating actions MUST accept an `Idempotency-Key` (Header for API, Field for Actions).
    16	  - **Format**: UUID v4.
    17	  - **Behavior**: Replaying an existing key returns the *original success response*.
    18	- **Pagination**: `page` (1-indexed) and `limit` (default: 20, max: 100). Response include `total`, `pages`, `hasNext`.
    19	
    20	### 1.2 Common Response Shapes
    21	**Success Response:**
    22	```json
    23	{
    24	  "data": { ... },
    25	  "warnings": Array<{ "code": string, "message": string }>
    26	}
    27	```
    28	
    29	**Error Response:**
    30	```json
    31	{
    32	  "error": {
    33	    "code": "string",
    34	    "message": "string",
    35	    "details": { "fields": Record<string, string[]> }
    36	  }
    37	}
    38	```
    39	
    40	---
    41	
    42	## 2. Auth & Admin Module (AUT)
    43	
    44	### 2.1 Session Lifecycle
    45	- **[POST] /actions/auth/login**: `{ email, password }` -> `{ user }`
    46	- **[POST] /actions/auth/logout**: `void`
    47	- **[GET] /api/auth/session**: -> `{ session: { user } }`
    48	
    49	### 2.2 Account Lifecycle
    50	- **[POST] /actions/auth/reset-password-request**: `{ email }`
    51	- **[POST] /actions/auth/reset-password-confirm**: `{ token, newPassword }`
    52	- **[POST] /actions/auth/request-export**: `{ format: 'JSON' | 'CSV' }` -> `{ requestId }`
    53	- **[POST] /actions/auth/schedule-deletion**: `{ passwordConfirmation }` -> `{ scheduledFor }`
    54	
    55	### 2.3 Managed Users (Admin)
    56	- **[GET] /api/admin/managed-users**: -> `{ items: ManagedUserDto[] }`
    57	- **[POST] /actions/auth/invite**: `{ email }` -> `{ inviteId, expiresAt }`
    58	
    59	---
    60	
    61	## 3. Tracker Module (TRK)
    62	
    63	### 3.1 Protocols
    64	- **[GET] /api/tracker/protocols**: `?status=ACTIVE` -> `{ items: ProtocolDto[] }`
    65	- **[POST] /actions/tracker/create-protocol**: `{ compoundId, dose, schedule, startDate, cycleId? }`
    66	- **[PATCH] /actions/tracker/update-protocol**: `{ id, status, dose, schedule }`
    67	
    68	### 3.2 Dose Logging
    69	- **[POST] /actions/tracker/log-dose**: 
    70	  - **Request**: `{ protocolId, scheduledDate, amount, status: 'LOGGED'|'SKIPPED', injectionSite?, note?, vialId? }`
    71	  - **Response**: `200 OK` with `warnings: ['insufficient_inventory']` if applicable.
    72	- **[POST] /actions/tracker/batch-log**: `{ logs: Array<DoseLogInput> }`
    73	
    74	### 3.3 PWA Sync
    75	- **[POST] /api/sync**:
    76	  - **Request**: `{ events: Array<SyncEvent> }`
    77	  - **Event Envelope**: `{ eventId, type: 'LOG_DOSE'|'EDIT_LOG'|'SKIP_DOSE', payload, occurredAt, timezone }`
    78	
    79	---
    80	
    81	## 4. Reconstitution Module (REC)
    82	
    83	### 4.1 Calculator
    84	- **[POST] /api/reconstitution/calculate**: `{ totalMg, bacWaterMl, targetDoseMcg }`
    85	- **Response**: `{ concentrationMcgPerMl, unitsPerDose, injectionVolMl, warnings: SafetyWarning[] }`
    86	
    87	### 4.2 Vial Inventory
    88	- **[GET] /api/reconstitution/vials**: `?status=ACTIVE` -> `{ items: VialDto[] }`
    89	- **[POST] /actions/reconstitution/save-vial**: `{ compoundId, totalMg, bacWaterMl?, expiresAt? }`
    90	
    91	---
    92	
    93	## 5. Ordering Module (ORD)
    94	
    95	### 5.1 Vendor Catalog
    96	- **[GET] /api/ordering/vendors**: -> `{ items: VendorDto[] }`
    97	- **[GET] /api/ordering/products**: `?vendorId=uuid` -> `{ items: ProductDto[] }`
    98	
    99	### 5.2 Order Lifecycle
   100	- **[POST] /actions/ordering/create-draft**: `{ vendorId, items: Array<{ productId, quantity }> }`
   101	- **[POST] /actions/ordering/send-order**: `{ orderId }` -> `{ telegramMessageId, fallbackText? }`
   102	- **[POST] /actions/ordering/confirm-quote**: `{ orderId, confirmedTotal, currency, walletAddress }` -> **Sent -> Confirmed**
   103	- **[POST] /actions/ordering/mark-paid**: `{ orderId, txId?, acknowledged: boolean }` -> **Confirmed -> PaymentSent**
   104	- **[POST] /actions/ordering/mark-received**: `{ orderId, itemsToInventory: Array<{ productId, vialDetails }> }`
   105	
   106	---
   107	
   108	## 6. Expanded Domain Error Catalog
   109	
   110	| Code | Status | Meaning |
   111	|------|--------|---------|
   112	| `validation_failed` | 400 | Payload fails Zod schema validation. |
   113	| `insufficient_permissions` | 403 | Managed user attempting Power User action. |
   114	| `protocol_not_found` | 404 | referenced protocol ID does not exist or is deleted. |
   115	| `invalid_order_transition` | 409 | e.g. Trying to mark a DRAFT order as PAID. |
   116	| `mtproto_connection_error` | 503 | Telegram service unreachable or session expired. |
   117	| `audit_write_failed` | 500 | Database transaction rolled back due to audit failure. |
   118	| `idempotency_key_conflict` | 409 | Key already used for a different payload. |
   119	
   120	---
   121	
   122	## 7. Sync Event Definition (TypeScript)
   123	
   124	```typescript
   125	type SyncEvent = {
   126	  eventId: string; // UUID v4 used as Idempotency-Key
   127	  type: 'LOG_DOSE' | 'SKIP_DOSE' | 'EDIT_DOSE';
   128	  payload: {
   129	    protocolId: string;
   130	    scheduledDate: string; // ISO Date
   131	    amount?: { value: number; unit: string };
   132	    injectionSite?: { location: string; group: string };
   133	    note?: string;
   134	  };
   135	  occurredAt: string; // ISO Timestamp
   136	  timezone: string;   // IANA Name
   137	};
   138	```

